0:10:19.26,000 --> 0:10:21,000
so I am, begrudgingly,

252
0:10:21.26,000 --> 0:10:24,000
almost a generation older than most of them.

253
0:10:24.26,000 --> 0:10:26,000
This is a generation

254
0:10:26.26,000 --> 0:10:29,000
that's grown up taking their voices pretty much for granted.

255
0:10:29.26,000 --> 0:10:31,000
They're not fighting that battle that we're all fighting

256
0:10:31.26,000 --> 0:10:33,000
about who gets to speak;

257
0:10:33.26,000 --> 0:10:35,000
they all get to speak.

258
0:10:35.26,000 --> 0:10:37,000
They can express their opinion

259
0:10:37.26,000 --> 0:10:39,000
on any channel at any time,

260
0:10:39.26,000 --> 0:10:41,000
and they do.

261
0:10:41.26,000 --> 0:10:44,000
So when they're faced with the problem of government,

262
0:10:44.26,000 --> 0:10:46,000
they don't care as much

263
0:10:46.26,000 --> 0:10:48,000
about using their voices.

264
0:10:48.26,000 --> 0:10:5,000
They're using their hands.

265
0:10:50.26,000 --> 0:10:52,000
They're using their hands

266
0:10:52.26,000 --> 0:10:55,000
to write applications that make government work better.

267
0:10:55.26,000 --> 0:10:58,000
And those applications let us use our hands

268
0:10:58.26,000 --> 0:11:01,000
to make our communities better.

269
0:11:01.26,000 --> 0:11:04,000
That could be shoveling out a hydrant, pulling a weed,

270
0:11:04.26,000 --> 0:11:08,000
turning over a garbage can with an opossum in it.

271
0:11:08.26,000 --> 0:11:11,000
And certainly, we could have been shoveling out those fire hydrants all along,

272
0:11:11.26,000 --> 0:11:13,000
and many people do.

273
0:11:13.26,000 --> 0:11:16,000
But these apps are like little digital reminders

274
0:11:16.26,000 --> 0:11:18,000
that we're not just consumers,

275
0:11:18.26,000 --> 0:11:2,000
and we're not just consumers of government,

276
0:11:20.26,000 --> 0:11:23,000
putting in our taxes and getting back services.

277
0:11:23.26,000 --> 0:11:25,000
We're more than that,

278
0:11:25.26,000 --> 0:11:27,000
we're citizens.

279
0:11:27.26,000 --> 0:11:3,000
And we're not going to fix government

280
0:11:30.26,000 --> 0:11:33,000
until we fix citizenship.

281
0:11:33.26,000 --> 0:11:37,000
So the question I have for all of you here:

282
0:11:37.26,000 --> 0:11:39,000
When it comes to the big, important things

283
0:11:39.26,000 --> 0:11:41,000
that we need to do together,

284
0:11:41.26,000 --> 0:11:43,000
all of us together,

285
0:11:43.26,000 --> 0:11:46,000
are we just going to be a crowd of voices,

286
0:11:46.26,000 --> 0:11:48,000
or are we also going to be

287
0:11:48.26,000 --> 0:11:5,000
a crowd of hands?

288
0:11:50.26,000 --> 0:11:52,000
Thank you.

289
0:11:52.26,000 --> 0:12:04,000
(Applause)

